# tt-metal version used by tt-lang.
# Sourceable shell snippet: shell consumers `. third-party/tt-metal-version`
# and read $TTNN_PYPI / $TTNN_PYPI_TT_METAL_TAG / $TT_METAL_TAG; setup.py
# reads TTNN_PYPI via a small regex parser.
#
# Variables:
#   TTNN_PYPI    - PyPI version of ttnn. setup.py uses it in the wheel's
#                  install_requires (ttnn == $TTNN_PYPI).
#   TTNN_PYPI_TT_METAL_TAG
#                - tt-metal git tag the ttnn PyPI release was built from.
#                  publish-pypi.yml requires this to match TT_METAL_TAG.
#   TT_METAL_TAG - tt-metal git tag tt-lang builds against.
#                  check-tt-metal-version.sh uses it to verify the
#                  third-party/tt-metal submodule HEAD;
#                  .github/containers/Dockerfile.base uses it to download
#                  install_dependencies.sh and SFPI info.
#
# Why separate tags: TTNN_PYPI_TT_METAL_TAG and TT_METAL_TAG may diverge.
# ttnn 0.70.1, for example, was built from tt-metal tag v0.70.1-rc1;
# tt-metal does not publish a v0.70.1 tag. To confirm which tt-metal tag a
# given ttnn release was built from, inspect the PyPI release's provenance
# attestation: https://pypi.org/project/ttnn/<version>/
#
# Bumping:
#   1. Update TTNN_PYPI and TTNN_PYPI_TT_METAL_TAG to match an existing ttnn
#      PyPI release and its underlying tt-metal tag.
#   2. Update TT_METAL_TAG to the tt-metal tag tt-lang should build against.
#   3. Run: .github/scripts/check-tt-metal-version.sh --update
#      to check out third-party/tt-metal at the matching commit.
#   4. Commit the version file and the submodule update together.
#
# Mismatch warning: the build verifies that third-party/tt-metal's SHA
# matches tt-mlir's TT_METAL_VERSION value. When a tt-mlir uplift requires
# a newer tt-metal than the released ttnn wheel was built from, the
# generated kernel may fail to compile (moved headers, renamed
# namespaces, etc.). Resolve by either: (a) carrying a patch under
# third-party/patches/ttmlir-*.patch that adapts the emission to the
# older tt-metal, or (b) passing -DTTLANG_ACCEPT_TTMETAL_MISMATCH=ON to
# CMake to develop against a newer tt-metal locally (releases must
# still align with the ttnn PyPI wheel).

TTNN_PYPI="0.70.1"
TTNN_PYPI_TT_METAL_TAG="v0.70.1-rc1"
# DANGER: public PyPI publish is blocked until TT_METAL_TAG matches
# TTNN_PYPI_TT_METAL_TAG. See docs/sphinx/build.md#publishing-to-s3-pypi.
TT_METAL_TAG="v0.71.0-rc2"
